	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=29371'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#336600;'>Cullis</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Journeyman<br>
			
				Posts: 103<br>
				
				Registered: 04-30-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=29371'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=907#M907">1</a> of 26
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 638 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Mages were, and have always been, the primary pet class of EQ.&nbsp; Even in VI literature it says that Mages have the most powerful pets and the widest variety of pets to fill different roles.&nbsp; Unfortunately the Mage pet, as the most powerful pet, has not been protected by the devs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Let me explain:</DIV>
<DIV>Warriors are hands down the best tanks in the game, in raids at least, no class can compete with them.</DIV>
<DIV>Clerics heal at roughly twice the ability of the next best healing class.</DIV>
<DIV>Wizards nuke at roughly twice the ability of the next best nuking class.</DIV>
<DIV>Rangers do ranged damage at hell I don't know, a LOT better than any other melee class. x5 maybe?</DIV>
<DIV>Rogues do huge sustained damage in comparison to other melees.</DIV>
<DIV>Enchanters can do crowd control better than any other class.</DIV>
<DIV>Mages, well mages are supposed to have the best pets.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There is no AA ability that lets any melee use a bow better than a Ranger.&nbsp; There is no charm spell or any other spell that lets anyone use a bow better than a ranger.</DIV>
<DIV>There is no AA ability that lets anyone of equal gear/xp heal better than a cleric.&nbsp; There is no charm spell or any other spell that lets any class heal better than a cleric.</DIV>
<DIV>No AA's or charms or what have you that lets any class nuke better than a wizard.</DIV>
<DIV>No AA's or charms or what have you that lets any class CC better than a Enchanter.&nbsp; Yes I know bards can mez, but Enchanters are the kings of it hands down.</DIV>
<DIV>No melee, with similar AA's or equipment can equal the situational damage of a rogue.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Yet Beastlords pets are near the mage pet&nbsp;in powerlevel.&nbsp; They are certainly more versatile as the beast can choose which spell his pet is going to proc.&nbsp; I hazard a guess that when we can parse the damage done by pet procs, bst pets will out damage a mage pet.</DIV>
<DIV>3 classes have an&nbsp;AA at L59-L60&nbsp;that let's them charm pets that are DECIDEDLY more powerful than mage pets L59-L60 and some would argue are more powerful than mage pets L61-L65.&nbsp; I will not argue this however, as I have not seen any parses.&nbsp; It is definitely true however, that DC pets have more hp than mage pets.</DIV>
<DIV>CoD and similar spells allow a charming class to have pets that are 10-25x more powerful than a mage pet.&nbsp; 2k dps anyone?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There will NEVER be a spell that lets an enchanter nuke for 10-25x the power of a wizard.</DIV>
<DIV>There will NEVER be an AA that lets a druid heal better than cleric.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>These things do not happen.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Why did&nbsp;it&nbsp;happen to mages?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>VI/SOE has gone out of its way to give almost&nbsp;every class a specific role that cannot be infringed upon, with the possible exception of the bard, which is supposed to be a jack of all trades.&nbsp; VI/SOE has taken great pains to protect those class roles.&nbsp; Yet the mage is no longer considered the primary pet class.&nbsp; Beastlords argue there is no such thing, while I have heard Enchanters and Wizards argue that Enchanters are the TRUE pet class.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mage pets need to be to the other pets, what the Wizard nuke is to other nukes, or what the Cleric heal is to other heals.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>06-04-2004</span> <span class=time_text>12:01 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
