			>
			<DIV>The difference between warder &amp; elemental performance all has to do with proc's &amp; buffs.&nbsp; The beastlord can boost their warder's DEX to incredibly high amounts which make for some serious spell spam v. mage not having any means to improve our elemental's base DEX any more than the +15 from our girdle.&nbsp; Also, the beastlord has awesome capability to boost warder ATK rating via direct +atk and +str so while on the surface it appears the warder is sub-par in melee due to max hit, the plethera of buffs a warder has access to makes it quite possibly the best performing pet.&nbsp; Somehow Dev's do not factor in the buffs warders have access to when it comes to performance v. elementals.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>When you throw mage toys into the equasion (available 24/7 for mere change) the warder becomes a proc'ing machine with max haste, and as long as the spells hit mobs warders seriously overtake even positioned water pets in overall DPS.</DIV>
