			Your actually off on your Cleric/Druid heal numbers and you should take Shaman healing into effect since they are a priest.  Priests have 2 types of heals, blast and 10sec.  The 10 sec heal for Clerics is complete heal while Druids and Shaman 10sec heals are for 75% max also and they dont recieve the same aa/foci bonuses as the blast heals.<br><br>10sec<br>Cleric Heal - Complete Heal: 7500<br>Druid Heal - Karana's Renewal: 4680/75% / 63% of cleric<br>Shaman Heal - Kragg's Mending: 1950/75% / 26% of cleric<br><br>Blast heals<br>Cleric Heal - Holy Light: 3275<br>Druid Heal - Sylvan Infusion: 2100 / 64% of cleric<br>Shaman Heal - Daluda's Mending: 1550 / 47% of cleric<br><br>Not only is a druid the 2nd best nuker (tied) in the game but they are also 2nd best healer.  Shamans heals, even w/focus and AAs, cant even compensate for 1 hit by a GoD mob.  On top of that, there 10sec heal has recieved no upgrade where they should have recieved a 3500 point/10 sec heal.<br><br>Unfortunatly the Mage and Shaman are the two classes most in need of recieving care/focus in what there purpose is.
