			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=37176'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=1068#M1068">25</a> of 26
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 270 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Cullis, this is a little late in replying, but here it goes.  <br><br>Shaman dont better slow.  In GoD, you have trash mobs that are at 25% by the time the debuff/slow hits.  Having a better slow does next to nothing.  Although there are 2 other classes that can slow almost as good (Chanter, Beastlord) and another that can slow enough for XP groups (Bard), the problem with the shaman is they have lost there place in this game.  <br><br>Shaman can do good DPS if they want.  Unfortunatly, there are two problems with a shaman doing this.  First, our DPS spells are terribly inefficient.  I can maintain DPS but will go OOM fast, even with a 6k+ mana pool.  Second is the aggro associated.  When Sony needed to make a chanters Tash spell high aggro but curable (pre remove curse btw), they gave it poison counters and set poison counters to be high aggro.  Now thats fine for a chanter who can crowd control.  But a Shaman get hosed because until LDoN all our good dots were Poison based.  I once managed to get 200+ dps on a mob for 30sec+.  This was DXXT in Vex Thal.  I stacked 5 dots onto him and got summoned rather quickly after.  Even if I had just used 2 poison dots for about 70ish DPS, I would have gotten summoned.  If there is any class that is summoned before a mage when a tank goes down on a raid its a shaman using dots.<br><br>The biggest problem with both our classes is Sonys attitude towards us.  When GoD 1st came out, Shaman had another useless disease dot.  Now the only time I use disease dots is on Emp Ssra, thats because nothing else but our insanely long cast time, low damage nuke hits him.  Shaman were up in arms about this.  So, after a month, Sony changed this dot to our new heal.  Its a 1650 point heal.  On top of that, its a heal that brings us back into line with sonys golden ratio (100/64/47 / cleric/druid/shaman).  So basically we got a spell we should have got in the 1st place and Sony, on these boards a few days ago, says these were big upgrades to help balance us.  I didnt know that giving us a spell in the first place would count as a big upgrade.<br><br>Some classes are currently whining to much about being ignored.  Rangers for example need minor fixes, but once you get elementals, they are balanced.  There melee DPS is greater then there Bow DPS but there bow DPS is the lowest aggro ranged DPS in the game.  I have been able to maintain 175+ dps on a raid mob that was wiping a raid (bad memblur on Ginto at 13% once).  That dps made the difference between the kill (6 or 8 people left in zone) and a wipe.  But overall were balanced.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Hunter <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=453758" target="_new">GrendalKhan Rose</a> - Forest Stalker<br>Elder <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=586374" target=_new">Teesa Zjoquor</a> - Prophet<br><a href="http://www.thewarcouncil.us/" target="_blank">The War Council</a> - Saryrn<br><br><strike>"The general shaman consensus, however, is that the lead spell designer is so wedded to his self-delusional notions of godhood, that he refuses to admit any error unless someone up the food chain from him stuffs a change down his throat." - Chutoi Dogslobber</strike>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
